<subSubSection id="42CAC4D94F77CD54EAFC12E1FC8B77CC" pageId="1" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="0A6F97524F77CD54EAFC12E1FC8B77CC" blockId="1.[136,1452,1478,2006]" pageId="1">
<emphasis id="38A44B404F77CD54EAFC12E1FE8775C4" bold="true" box="[136,265,1478,1502]" pageId="1">Discussion:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="CDD0ECD14F77CD54EB5012E1FE5575C4" authorityName="Hedge" authorityYear="1968" box="[292,475,1478,1502]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Cyphocardamum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="38A44B404F77CD54EB5012E1FE5575C4" box="[292,475,1478,1502]" italics="true" pageId="1">Cyphocardamum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="CDD0ECD14F77CD54E87A12E1FD0875C4" authorityName="Boelcke" authorityYear="1951" box="[526,646,1478,1502]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Lithodraba" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="38A44B404F77CD54E87A12E1FD0875C4" box="[526,646,1478,1502]" italics="true" pageId="1">Lithodraba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resemble 
<taxonomicName id="CDD0ECD14F77CD54E88712E1FCD675C4" box="[755,856,1478,1502]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Lepidium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="38A44B404F77CD54E88712E1FCD675C4" box="[755,856,1478,1502]" italics="true" pageId="1">Lepidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having angustiseptate, dehiscent fruits with 1-seeded locules, and they are typically pulvinate, a feature rather rare in 
<taxonomicName id="CDD0ECD14F77CD54E93012CDFC277618" box="[836,937,1514,1538]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Lepidium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="38A44B404F77CD54E93012CDFC277618" box="[836,937,1514,1538]" italics="true" pageId="1">Lepidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, 
<taxonomicName id="CDD0ECD14F77CD54EE5312CCFAD17618" authority="Watson (1871: 30)" authorityName="Watson" authorityPageNumber="30" authorityYear="1871" box="[1063,1375,1514,1538]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Lepidium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nanum">
<emphasis id="38A44B404F77CD54EE5312CCFB007618" box="[1063,1166,1515,1538]" italics="true" pageId="1">L. nanum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="6E41EAA34F77CD54EEE212CDFAD17618" author="Watson, S." box="[1174,1375,1514,1538]" pageId="1" refId="ref3224" refString="Watson, S. (1871) Botany [United States Geological Exploration of the Fortieth Parallel]. Washington [D. C.]: Government Printing Office, 525 pp." type="book" year="1871">Watson (1871: 30)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="CDD0ECD14F77CD54EFE212CCFDAE763C" authority="Welsh &amp; Goodrich (1980: 80)" authorityName="Welsh &amp; Goodrich" authorityPageNumber="80" authorityYear="1980" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Lepidium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ostleri">
<emphasis id="38A44B404F77CD54EFE212CCFF42763C" italics="true" pageId="1">L. ostleri</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="6E41EAA34F77CD54EAA11129FDAE763C" author="Welsh, S. L. &amp; Goodrich, S." box="[213,544,1550,1574]" pageId="1" pagination="78 - 88" refId="ref3258" refString="Welsh, S. L. &amp; Goodrich, S. (1980) Miscellaneous plant novelties from Alaska, Nevada, and Utah. Great Basin Naturalist 40: 78 - 88." type="journal article" year="1980">Welsh &amp; Goodrich (1980: 80)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
are narrowly endemic pulvinate species in the western 
<collectingCountry id="72C7D7C24F77CD54EEFD1129FA95763C" box="[1161,1307,1550,1574]" name="United States of America" pageId="1">United States</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="6E41EAA34F77CD54EF581129FEC47650" author="Al-Shehbaz, I. A. &amp; Gaskin, J. F." pageId="1" pagination="570 - 595" refId="ref1674" refString="Al-Shehbaz, I. A. &amp; Gaskin, J. F. (2010) Lepidium. In: Flora of North America Editorial Committee, Flora of North America (Eds.) Flora of North America North of Mexico vol. 7. Oxford University Press, New York, pp. 570 - 595." type="book chapter" year="2010">Al-Shehbaz and Gaskin, 2010</bibRefCitation>
). Both genera differ from 
<taxonomicName id="CDD0ECD14F77CD54E8121115FD457650" box="[614,715,1586,1610]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Lepidium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="38A44B404F77CD54E8121115FD457650" box="[614,715,1586,1610]" italics="true" pageId="1">Lepidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the scapose habit with few-flowered racemes (
<taxonomicName id="CDD0ECD14F77CD54EE981115FA2D7650" authorityName="Hedge" authorityYear="1968" box="[1260,1443,1586,1610]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Cyphocardamum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="38A44B404F77CD54EE981115FA2D7650" box="[1260,1443,1586,1610]" italics="true" pageId="1">Cyphocardamum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) or solitary flowers (
<taxonomicName id="CDD0ECD14F77CD54EB291171FE5B7674" authorityName="Boelcke" authorityYear="1951" box="[349,469,1622,1646]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Lithodraba" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="38A44B404F77CD54EB291171FE5B7674" box="[349,469,1622,1646]" italics="true" pageId="1">Lithodraba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and this “key” difference was used by 
<bibRefCitation id="6E41EAA34F77CD54E9FD1171FB377674" author="Appel, O. &amp; Al-Shehbaz, I. A." box="[905,1209,1622,1646]" pageId="1" pagination="75 - 174" refId="ref1832" refString="Appel, O. &amp; Al-Shehbaz, I. A. (2003) Cruciferae. In: Kubitzki, K. &amp; Bayer, C. (Eds.) Families and Genera of Vascular Plants. Vol. 5. Berlin &amp; Heidelberg: Springer-Verlag, pp. 75 - 174. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / 978 - 3 - 662 - 07255 - 4 _ 17" type="book chapter" year="2003">Appel &amp; Al-Shehbaz (2003)</bibRefCitation>
to separate them from 
<taxonomicName id="CDD0ECD14F77CD54EAFC115DFF637688" box="[136,237,1658,1682]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Lepidium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="38A44B404F77CD54EAFC115DFF637688" box="[136,237,1658,1682]" italics="true" pageId="1">Lepidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, both 
<taxonomicName id="CDD0ECD14F77CD54EBD4115CFD8B7688" authorityName="Watson" authorityYear="1871" box="[416,517,1659,1682]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Lepidium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nanum">
<emphasis id="38A44B404F77CD54EBD4115CFD8B7688" box="[416,517,1659,1682]" italics="true" pageId="1">L. nanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="CDD0ECD14F77CD54E84E115CFD147688" authorityName="Welsh &amp; Goodrich" authorityYear="1980" box="[570,666,1658,1682]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Lepidium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ostleri">
<emphasis id="38A44B404F77CD54E84E115CFD147688" box="[570,666,1658,1682]" italics="true" pageId="1">L. ostleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are scapose, and this single feature (scapose vs. non-scapose) alone does not justify the recognition of genera in the 
<taxonomicName id="CDD0ECD14F77CD54E82C11B9FD6B76AC" box="[600,741,1694,1718]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Brassicaceae</taxonomicName>
. For example, 
<taxonomicName id="CDD0ECD14F77CD54E9F211B9FA2576AC" authority="Andrzejowski ex Candolle (1824: 209)" authorityName="Candolle" authorityPageNumber="209" authorityYear="1824" box="[902,1451,1694,1718]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Aphragmus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="38A44B404F77CD54E9F211B9FB8F76AC" box="[902,1025,1694,1718]" italics="true" pageId="1">Aphragmus</emphasis>
Andrzejowski ex 
<bibRefCitation id="6E41EAA34F77CD54EEB111B9FA2576AC" author="Candolle, A. P. de" box="[1221,1451,1694,1718]" pageId="1" pagination="132 - 236" refId="ref2006" refString="Candolle, A. P. de (1824) Prodromus systematis naturalis regni vegetabilis, vol. 1. Parisiis [Paris]: Sumptibus Sociorum Treuttel et Wurtz, [Cruciferae], pp. 132 - 236." type="book chapter" year="1824">Candolle (1824: 209)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
has species with well-developed racemes and others with solitary flowers from a basal rosette. Furthermore, most species of 
<taxonomicName id="CDD0ECD14F77CD54EAFC11C1FE7E76E4" authority="Torrey (1837: 87)" authorityName="Torrey" authorityPageNumber="87" authorityYear="1837" box="[136,496,1766,1790]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Leavenworthia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="38A44B404F77CD54EAFC11C1FEA676E4" box="[136,296,1766,1790]" italics="true" pageId="1">Leavenworthia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="6E41EAA34F77CD54EB4411C1FE7E76E4" author="Torrey, J." box="[304,496,1766,1790]" pageId="1" pagination="80 - 94" refId="ref2847" refString="Torrey, J. (1837) An account of several new genera and species of North American plants. Annals of the Lyceum of Natural History of New York 4: 80 - 94. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1749 - 6632.1848. tb 00266. x" type="journal article" year="1837">Torrey (1837: 87)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
produce solitary flowers and/or well-developed racemes on the same plant (see 
<bibRefCitation id="6E41EAA34F77CD54EF2C11C1FF4F7738" author="Rollins, R. C." pageId="1" pagination="3 - 98" refId="ref2459" refString="Rollins, R. C. (1963) The evolution and systematics of Leavenworthia (Cruciferae). Contributions from the Gray Herbarium 192: 3 - 98." type="journal article" year="1963">Rollins, 1963</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="6E41EAA34F77CD54EAA0102DFEE67738" author="Hedge, I." box="[212,360,1802,1826]" pageId="1" pagination="63 - 122" refId="ref2257" refString="Hedge, I. (1968) Lepidieae. In: Rechinger, K. H. (Ed.) Flora Iranica vol. 57. Akademische Druch- u. Verlagsanstalt, Graz, pp. 63 - 122." type="book chapter" year="1968">Hedge (1968)</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName id="CDD0ECD14F77CD54EB9E102DFD2F7738" authorityName="Hedge" authorityYear="1968" box="[490,673,1802,1826]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Cyphocardamum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="38A44B404F77CD54EB9E102DFD2F7738" box="[490,673,1802,1826]" italics="true" pageId="1">Cyphocardamum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="CDD0ECD14F77CD54E9D6102DFAF07738" authority="Karelin &amp; Kirilow (1841: 386)" authorityName="Karelin &amp; Kirilow" authorityPageNumber="386" authorityYear="1841" box="[930,1406,1802,1826]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Stroganowia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="38A44B404F77CD54E9D6102DFBA7773B" box="[930,1065,1802,1825]" italics="true" pageId="1">Stroganowia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="6E41EAA34F77CD54EE45102DFAF07738" author="Karelin, G. &amp; Kirilow, J." box="[1073,1406,1802,1826]" pageId="1" pagination="703 - 870" refId="ref2298" refString="Karelin, G. &amp; Kirilow, J. (1841) Enumeratio plantarum anno 1840 in regionibus Altaicis et confinibus collectarum. Bulletin de la Societe Imperiale des Naturalistes de Moscou 14 (3): 369 - 459; 14 (4): 703 - 870." type="journal article" year="1841">Karelin &amp; Kirilow (1841: 386)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but it is generally agreed that the latter genus is indistinguishable from 
<taxonomicName id="CDD0ECD14F77CD54E91B1009FC5A775C" box="[879,980,1838,1862]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Lepidium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="38A44B404F77CD54E91B1009FC5A775C" box="[879,980,1838,1862]" italics="true" pageId="1">Lepidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and was united with it nearly two decades ago (
<bibRefCitation id="6E41EAA34F77CD54EAC91075FE4D7770" author="Al-Shehbaz, I. A. &amp; Mummenhoff, K. &amp; Appel, O." box="[189,451,1874,1898]" pageId="1" pagination="5 - 11" refId="ref1733" refString="Al-Shehbaz, I. A., Mummenhoff, K. &amp; Appel, O. (2002) Cardaria, Coronopus and Stroganowia are united with Lepidium (Brassicaceae). Novon 12: 5 - 11." type="journal article" year="2002">
Al-Shehbaz 
<emphasis id="38A44B404F77CD54EB311074FEF57770" box="[325,379,1874,1898]" italics="true" pageId="1">et al.</emphasis>
, 2002
</bibRefCitation>
). Although some pulvinate plants in the family produce numerous flowers, none comes even close to those of 
<taxonomicName id="CDD0ECD14F77CD54EB311050FE767794" box="[325,504,1910,1934]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Lepidium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mendocinense">
<emphasis id="38A44B404F77CD54EB311050FE767794" box="[325,504,1910,1934]" italics="true" pageId="1">L. mendocinense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in which a single plant may have more than 4,000 flowers (
<figureCitation id="92EB8BD74F77CD54EE0E1051FB587794" box="[1146,1238,1910,1934]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[136,229,1407,1429]" captionTargetBox="[318,1270,617,1381]" captionTargetId="figure-175@1.[318,1270,617,1381]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Plant of Lepidium mendocinense with 4,217 opened flowers. Photo by Anibal O. Prina." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5317576" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5317576/files/figure.png" pageId="1">Figure 1</figureCitation>
). In conclusion, the recognition of 
<taxonomicName id="CDD0ECD14F77CD54EB5110BDFE5277A8" authorityName="Hedge" authorityYear="1968" box="[293,476,1946,1970]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Cyphocardamum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="38A44B404F77CD54EB5110BDFE5277A8" box="[293,476,1946,1970]" italics="true" pageId="1">Cyphocardamum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="CDD0ECD14F77CD54E87B10BDFD0977A8" authorityName="Boelcke" authorityYear="1951" box="[527,647,1946,1970]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Lithodraba" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="38A44B404F77CD54E87B10BDFD0977A8" box="[527,647,1946,1970]" italics="true" pageId="1">Lithodraba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as distinct from 
<taxonomicName id="CDD0ECD14F77CD54E94E10BDFC1177A8" box="[826,927,1946,1970]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Lepidium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="38A44B404F77CD54E94E10BDFC1177A8" box="[826,927,1946,1970]" italics="true" pageId="1">Lepidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not supported by molecular data or by a single feature that consistently separates them from the last genus.
</paragraph>
